cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the problem of finding optimal neural architecture designs for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method that aggregates two main results of the previous state-of-the-art in neural architecture search, which involves machine learning techniques such as sequential model-based optimization (SMBO) and weight-sharing. Hence, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of neural architectures, which is a sub-field of neural networks, and hence could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves experiments on the CIFAR-10 dataset, which is a popular benchmark dataset in the field of computer vision and machine learning, and hence could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
